.ie n .SS "quadray""(D,f,{""\fIflag\fP"" = 0})"""
.el .SS "quadray\f(CW(D,f,{\fP\fIflag\fP\f(CW = 0})\fP"
.IX Xref "quadray"
.IX Subsection "quadray(D,f,{flag = 0})"
relative equation for the ray class
field of conductor \f(CW\*(C`f\*(C'\fR for the quadratic field of discriminant \f(CW\*(C`D\*(C'\fR (which
can also be a \f(CW\*(C`bnf\*(C'\fR), using analytic methods.
.PP
For \f(CW\*(C`D < 0\*(C'\fR, uses the \fIsigma\fR function. \fIflag\fR has the following meaning: if
it's an odd integer, outputs instead the vector of \f(CW\*(C`[\*(C'\fR\fIideal\fR\f(CW\*(C`,
\&\*(C'\fR\fIcorresponding root\fR\f(CW\*(C`]\*(C'\fR. It can also be a two-component vector
\&\f(CW\*(C`[\*(C'\fR\fIlambda\fR\f(CW\*(C`,\*(C'\fR\fIflag\fR\f(CW\*(C`]\*(C'\fR, where \fIflag\fR is as above and \fIlambda\fR is the technical
element of \f(CW\*(C`bnf\*(C'\fR necessary for Schertz's method. In that case, returns
0 if \fIlambda\fR is not suitable.
