.ie n .SS "bnrL1""(""\fIbnr\fP"",""\fIsubgroup\fP"",{""\fIflag\fP"" = 0})"""
.el .SS "bnrL1\f(CW(\fP\fIbnr\fP\f(CW,\fP\fIsubgroup\fP\f(CW,{\fP\fIflag\fP\f(CW = 0})\fP"
.IX Xref "bnrL1"
.IX Subsection "bnrL1(bnr,subgroup,{flag = 0})"
\&\fIbnr\fR being the number field data which is output by
\&\f(CW\*(C`bnrinit(,,1)\*(C'\fR and \fIsubgroup\fR being a square matrix defining a
congruence subgroup of the ray class group corresponding to \fIbnr\fR
(or \f(CW0\fR for the trivial congruence subgroup), returns for each
character \fIchi\fR of the ray class group which is trivial on this
subgroup, the value at \f(CW\*(C`s = 1\*(C'\fR (or \f(CW\*(C`s = 0\*(C'\fR) of the abelian
\&\f(CW\*(C`L\*(C'\fR\-function associated to \fIchi\fR. For the value at \f(CW\*(C`s = 0\*(C'\fR, the
function returns in fact for each character \fIchi\fR a vector \f(CW\*(C`[r_\*(C'\fR\fIchi\fR\f(CW\*(C` ,
c_\*(C'\fR\fIchi\fR\f(CW\*(C`]\*(C'\fR where \f(CW\*(C`r_\*(C'\fR\fIchi\fR is the order of \f(CW\*(C`L(s, \*(C'\fR\fIchi\fR\f(CW\*(C`)\*(C'\fR at \f(CW\*(C`s = 0\*(C'\fR and
\&\f(CW\*(C`c_\*(C'\fR\fIchi\fR the first non-zero term in the expansion of \f(CW\*(C`L(s,
\&\*(C'\fR\fIchi\fR\f(CW\*(C`)\*(C'\fR at \f(CW\*(C`s = 0\*(C'\fR; in other words
.IX Xref "character"
.PP
\&\ \ \f(CW\*(C`L(s, \*(C'\fR\fIchi\fR\f(CW\*(C`) = c_\*(C'\fR\fIchi\fR\f(CW\*(C`.s^{r_\*(C'\fR\fIchi\fR\f(CW\*(C`} + O(s^{r_\*(C'\fR\fIchi\fR\f(CW\*(C` + 1})\*(C'\fR
.PP
near \f(CW0\fR. \fIflag\fR is optional, default value is 0; its binary digits
mean 1: compute at \f(CW\*(C`s = 1\*(C'\fR if set to 1 or \f(CW\*(C`s = 0\*(C'\fR if set to 0, 2: compute
the primitive \f(CW\*(C`L\*(C'\fR\-functions associated to \fIchi\fR if set to 0 or the
\&\f(CW\*(C`L\*(C'\fR\-function with Euler factors at prime ideals dividing the modulus of
\&\fIbnr\fR removed if set to 1 (this is the so-called \f(CW\*(C`L_S(s, \*(C'\fR\fIchi\fR\f(CW\*(C`)\*(C'\fR
function where \f(CW\*(C`S\*(C'\fR is the set of infinite places of the number field
together with the finite prime ideals dividing the modulus of \fIbnr\fR,
see the example below), 3: returns also the character.
.PP
Example:
.PP
.Vb 3
\&  bnf = bnfinit(x^2 \- 229);
\&  bnr = bnrinit(bnf,1,1);
\&  bnrL1(bnr, 0)
.Ve
.PP
returns the order and the first non-zero term of the abelian
\&\f(CW\*(C`L\*(C'\fR\-functions \f(CW\*(C`L(s, \*(C'\fR\fIchi\fR\f(CW\*(C`)\*(C'\fR at \f(CW\*(C`s = 0\*(C'\fR where \fIchi\fR runs through the
characters of the class group of \fBQ\fR\f(CW\*(C`(\*(C'\fR \fIsqrt\fR \f(CW\*(C`{229})\*(C'\fR. Then
.PP
.Vb 2
\&  bnr2 = bnrinit(bnf,2,1);
\&  bnrL1(bnr2,0,2)
.Ve
.PP
returns the order and the first non-zero terms of the abelian
\&\f(CW\*(C`L\*(C'\fR\-functions \f(CW\*(C`L_S(s, \*(C'\fR\fIchi\fR\f(CW\*(C`)\*(C'\fR at \f(CW\*(C`s = 0\*(C'\fR where \fIchi\fR runs through the
characters of the class group of \fBQ\fR\f(CW\*(C`(\*(C'\fR \fIsqrt\fR \f(CW\*(C`{229})\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`S\*(C'\fR is the set
of infinite places of \fBQ\fR\f(CW\*(C`(\*(C'\fR \fIsqrt\fR \f(CW\*(C`{229})\*(C'\fR together with the finite prime
\&\f(CW2\fR (note that the ray class group modulo \f(CW2\fR is in fact the class
group, so \f(CW\*(C`bnrL1(bnr2,0)\*(C'\fR returns exactly the same answer as
\&\f(CW\*(C`bnrL1(bnr,0)\*(C'\fR!).
.PP
The library syntax is \fBbnrL1\fR\f(CW\*(C`(\*(C'\fR\fIbnr\fR\f(CW\*(C`,\*(C'\fR\fIsubgroup\fR\f(CW\*(C`,\*(C'\fR\fIflag\fR\f(CW\*(C`,\*(C'\fR\fIprec\fR\f(CW\*(C`)\*(C'\fR
.IX Xref "bnrL1"
.ie n .SS "bnrclass""(""\fIbnf\fP"",""\fIideal\fP"",{""\fIflag\fP"" = 0})"""
.el .SS "bnrclass\f(CW(\fP\fIbnf\fP\f(CW,\fP\fIideal\fP\f(CW,{\fP\fIflag\fP\f(CW = 0})\fP"
.IX Xref "bnrclass"
.IX Subsection "bnrclass(bnf,ideal,{flag = 0})"
\&\fIbnf\fR being a big number field
as output by \f(CW\*(C`bnfinit\*(C'\fR (the units are mandatory unless the ideal is
trivial), and \fIideal\fR being either an ideal in any form or a two-component
row vector containing an ideal and an \f(CW\*(C`r_1\*(C'\fR\-component row vector of flags
indicating which real Archimedean embeddings to take in the module, computes
the ray class group of the number field for the module \fIideal\fR, as a
3\-component vector as all other finite Abelian groups (cardinality, vector of
cyclic components, corresponding generators).
.PP
If \fIflag\fR\f(CW\*(C` = 2\*(C'\fR, the output is different. It is a 6\-component vector \f(CW\*(C`w\*(C'\fR. \f(CW\*(C`w[1]\*(C'\fR
is \fIbnf\fR. \f(CW\*(C`w[2]\*(C'\fR is the result of applying
\&\f(CW\*(C`idealstar(\*(C'\fR\fIbnf\fR\f(CW\*(C`,I,2)\*(C'\fR. \f(CW\*(C`w[3]\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`w[4]\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`w[6]\*(C'\fR are technical
components used only by the function \f(CW\*(C`bnrisprincipal\*(C'\fR. \f(CW\*(C`w[5]\*(C'\fR is the
structure of the ray class group as would have been output with \fIflag\fR\f(CW\*(C` = 0\*(C'\fR.
.PP
If \fIflag\fR\f(CW\*(C` = 1\*(C'\fR, as above, except that the generators of the ray class group are
not computed, which saves time.
.PP
The library syntax is \fBbnrclass0\fR\f(CW\*(C`(\*(C'\fR\fIbnf\fR\f(CW\*(C`,\*(C'\fR\fIideal\fR\f(CW\*(C`,\*(C'\fR\fIflag\fR\f(CW\*(C`,\*(C'\fR\fIprec\fR\f(CW\*(C`)\*(C'\fR.
.IX Xref "bnrclass0"
.ie n .SS "bnrclassno""(""\fIbnf\fP"",I)"""
.el .SS "bnrclassno\f(CW(\fP\fIbnf\fP\f(CW,I)\fP"
.IX Xref "bnrclassno"
.IX Subsection "bnrclassno(bnf,I)"
\&\fIbnf\fR being a big number field
as output
by \f(CW\*(C`bnfinit\*(C'\fR (units are mandatory unless the ideal is trivial), and \f(CW\*(C`I\*(C'\fR
being either an ideal in any form or a two-component row vector containing an
ideal and an \f(CW\*(C`r_1\*(C'\fR\-component row vector of flags indicating which real
Archimedean embeddings to take in the modulus, computes the ray class number
of the number field for the modulus \f(CW\*(C`I\*(C'\fR. This is faster than \f(CW\*(C`bnrclass\*(C'\fR
and should be used if only the ray class number is desired.
.PP
The library syntax is \fBrayclassno\fR\f(CW\*(C`(\*(C'\fR\fIbnf\fR\f(CW\*(C`,I)\*(C'\fR.
.IX Xref "rayclassno"
.ie n .SS "bnrclassnolist""(""\fIbnf\fP"",""\fIlist\fP"")"""
