.ie n .SS "factornf""(x,t)"""
.el .SS "factornf\f(CW(x,t)\fP"
.IX Xref "factornf"
.IX Subsection "factornf(x,t)"
factorization of the univariate polynomial \f(CW\*(C`x\*(C'\fR
over the number field defined by the (univariate) polynomial \f(CW\*(C`t\*(C'\fR. \f(CW\*(C`x\*(C'\fR may
have coefficients in \fBQ\fR or in the number field. The main variable of
\&\f(CW\*(C`t\*(C'\fR must be of \fIlower\fR priority than that of \f(CW\*(C`x\*(C'\fR (in other words the
variable number of \f(CW\*(C`t\*(C'\fR must be \fIgreater\fR than that of \f(CW\*(C`x\*(C'\fR). However if
the coefficients of the number field occur explicitly (as polmods) as
coefficients of \f(CW\*(C`x\*(C'\fR, the variable of these polmods \fImust\fR be the same as
the main variable of \f(CW\*(C`t\*(C'\fR. For example
.PP
.Vb 4
\&  ? factornf(x^2 + Mod(y, y^2+1), y^2+1);
\&  ? factornf(x^2 + 1, y^2+1); \e\e these two are OK
\&  ? factornf(x^2 + Mod(z,z^2+1), y^2+1)
\&    ***   incorrect type in gmulsg
.Ve
.PP
The library syntax is \fBpolfnf\fR\f(CW\*(C`(x,t)\*(C'\fR.
.IX Xref "polfnf"
.ie n .SS "galoisfixedfield""(""\fIgal\fP"",""\fIperm\fP"",{fl = 0},{v = y}))"""
.el .SS "galoisfixedfield\f(CW(\fP\fIgal\fP\f(CW,\fP\fIperm\fP\f(CW,{fl = 0},{v = y}))\fP"
.IX Xref "galoisfixedfield"
.IX Subsection "galoisfixedfield(gal,perm,{fl = 0},{v = y}))"
\&\fIgal\fR being be a Galois field as output by \f(CW\*(C`galoisinit\*(C'\fR and
\&\fIperm\fR an element of \fIgal\fR\f(CW\*(C`.group\*(C'\fR or a vector of such elements,
computes the fixed field of \fIgal\fR by the automorphism defined by the
permutations \fIperm\fR of the roots \fIgal\fR\f(CW\*(C`.roots\*(C'\fR. \f(CW\*(C`P\*(C'\fR is guaranteed to
be squarefree modulo \fIgal\fR\f(CW\*(C`.p\*(C'\fR.
.IX Xref "galoisinit"
.PP
If no flags or \fIflag\fR\f(CW\*(C` = 0\*(C'\fR, output format is the same as for \f(CW\*(C`nfsubfield\*(C'\fR,
returning \f(CW\*(C`[P,x]\*(C'\fR such that \f(CW\*(C`P\*(C'\fR is a polynomial defining the fixed field, and
\&\f(CW\*(C`x\*(C'\fR is a root of \f(CW\*(C`P\*(C'\fR expressed as a polmod in \fIgal\fR\f(CW\*(C`.pol\*(C'\fR.
.IX Xref "nfsubfield"
.PP
If \fIflag\fR\f(CW\*(C` = 1\*(C'\fR return only the polynomial \f(CW\*(C`P\*(C'\fR.
.PP
If \fIflag\fR\f(CW\*(C` = 2\*(C'\fR return \f(CW\*(C`[P,x,F]\*(C'\fR where \f(CW\*(C`P\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`x\*(C'\fR are as above and \f(CW\*(C`F\*(C'\fR is the
factorization of \fIgal\fR\f(CW\*(C`.pol\*(C'\fR over the field defined by \f(CW\*(C`P\*(C'\fR, where
variable \f(CW\*(C`v\*(C'\fR (\f(CW\*(C`y\*(C'\fR by default) stands for a root of \f(CW\*(C`P\*(C'\fR. The priority of \f(CW\*(C`v\*(C'\fR
must be less than the priority of the variable of \fIgal\fR\f(CW\*(C`.pol\*(C'\fR.
.PP
Example:
.PP
.Vb 3
\&  G = galoisinit(x^4+1);
\&  galoisfixedfield(G,G.group[2],2)
\&    [x^2 + 2, Mod(x^3 + x, x^4 + 1), [x^2 \- y*x \- 1, x^2 + y*x \- 1]]
.Ve
.PP
computes the factorization  \f(CW\*(C`x^4+1 = (x^2\-\*(C'\fR \fIsqrt\fR \f(CW\*(C`{\-2}x\-1)(x^2+\*(C'\fR \fIsqrt\fR \f(CW\*(C`{\-2}x\-1)\*(C'\fR
.PP
The library syntax is \fBgaloisfixedfield\fR\f(CW\*(C`(\*(C'\fR\fIgal\fR\f(CW\*(C`,\*(C'\fR\fIperm\fR\f(CW\*(C`,p)\*(C'\fR.
.IX Xref "galoisfixedfield"
.ie n .SS "galoisinit""(""\fIpol\fP"",{den})"""
.el .SS "galoisinit\f(CW(\fP\fIpol\fP\f(CW,{den})\fP"
.IX Xref "galoisinit"
.IX Subsection "galoisinit(pol,{den})"
computes the Galois group
and all neccessary information for computing the fixed fields of the
Galois extension \f(CW\*(C`K/\*(C'\fR\fBQ\fR where \f(CW\*(C`K\*(C'\fR is the number field defined by
\&\fIpol\fR (monic irreducible polynomial in \fBZ\fR\f(CW\*(C`[X]\*(C'\fR or
a number field as output by \f(CW\*(C`nfinit\*(C'\fR). The extension \f(CW\*(C`K/\*(C'\fR\fBQ\fR must be
Galois with Galois group ``weakly'' super-solvable (see \f(CW\*(C`nfgaloisconj\*(C'\fR)
.IX Xref "nfinit nfgaloisconj"
.PP
\&\fBWarning:\fR The interface of this function is experimental,
so the described output can be subject to important changes in the
near future. However the function itself should work as described. For any
remarks about this interface, please mail \f(CW\*(C`allomber@math.u\-bordeaux.fr\*(C'\fR.
.PP
The output is an 8\-component vector \fIgal\fR.
.PP
\&\fIgal\fR\f(CW\*(C`[1]\*(C'\fR contains the polynomial \fIpol\fR
(\fIgal\fR\f(CW\*(C`.pol\*(C'\fR).
.PP
\&\fIgal\fR\f(CW\*(C`[2]\*(C'\fR is a three\*(--components vector \f(CW\*(C`[p,e,q]\*(C'\fR where \f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR is a
prime number (\fIgal\fR\f(CW\*(C`.p\*(C'\fR) such that \fIpol\fR totally split
modulo \f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR , \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR is an integer and \f(CW\*(C`q = p^e\*(C'\fR (\fIgal\fR\f(CW\*(C`.mod\*(C'\fR) is the
modulus of the roots in \fIgal\fR\f(CW\*(C`.roots\*(C'\fR.
.PP
\&\fIgal\fR\f(CW\*(C`[3]\*(C'\fR is a vector \f(CW\*(C`L\*(C'\fR containing the \f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR\-adic roots of
\&\fIpol\fR as integers implicitly modulo \fIgal\fR\f(CW\*(C`.mod\*(C'\fR.
(\fIgal\fR\f(CW\*(C`.roots\*(C'\fR).
.PP
\&\fIgal\fR\f(CW\*(C`[4]\*(C'\fR is the inverse of the Van der Monde matrix of the
\&\f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR\-adic roots of \fIpol\fR, multiplied by \fIgal\fR\f(CW\*(C`[5]\*(C'\fR.
.PP
\&\fIgal\fR\f(CW\*(C`[5]\*(C'\fR is a multiple of the least common denominator of the
automorphisms expressed as polynomial in a root of \fIpol\fR.
.PP
\&\fIgal\fR\f(CW\*(C`[6]\*(C'\fR is the Galois group \f(CW\*(C`G\*(C'\fR expressed as a vector of
permutations of \f(CW\*(C`L\*(C'\fR (\fIgal\fR\f(CW\*(C`.group\*(C'\fR).
.PP
\&\fIgal\fR\f(CW\*(C`[7]\*(C'\fR is a generating subset \f(CW\*(C`S = [s_1,...,s_g]\*(C'\fR of \f(CW\*(C`G\*(C'\fR
expressed as a vector of permutations of \f(CW\*(C`L\*(C'\fR (\fIgal\fR\f(CW\*(C`.gen\*(C'\fR).
.PP
\&\fIgal\fR\f(CW\*(C`[8]\*(C'\fR contains the relative orders \f(CW\*(C`[o_1,...,o_g]\*(C'\fR of
the generators of \f(CW\*(C`S\*(C'\fR (\fIgal\fR\f(CW\*(C`.orders\*(C'\fR).
.PP
Let \f(CW\*(C`H\*(C'\fR be the maximal normal supersolvable subgroup of \f(CW\*(C`G\*(C'\fR, we have the
following properties:
.PP
\&\ \ \fB*\fR if \f(CW\*(C`G/H ~  A_4\*(C'\fR then \f(CW\*(C`[o_1,...,o_g]\*(C'\fR ends by
\&\f(CW\*(C`[2,2,3]\*(C'\fR.
.PP
\&\ \ \fB*\fR if \f(CW\*(C`G/H ~  S_4\*(C'\fR then \f(CW\*(C`[o_1,...,o_g]\*(C'\fR ends by
\&\f(CW\*(C`[2,2,3,2]\*(C'\fR.
.PP
\&\ \ \fB*\fR else \f(CW\*(C`G\*(C'\fR is super-solvable.
.PP
\&\ \ \fB*\fR for \f(CW\*(C`1 <= i <= g\*(C'\fR the subgroup of \f(CW\*(C`G\*(C'\fR generated by
\&\f(CW\*(C`[s_1,...,s_g]\*(C'\fR is normal, with the exception of \f(CW\*(C`i = g\-2\*(C'\fR in the
second case and of \f(CW\*(C`i = g\-3\*(C'\fR in the third.
.PP
\&\ \ \fB*\fR the relative order \f(CW\*(C`o_i\*(C'\fR of \f(CW\*(C`s_i\*(C'\fR is its order in the
quotient group \f(CW\*(C`G/<s_1,...,s_{i\-1}>\*(C'\fR, with the same
exceptions.
.PP
\&\ \ \fB*\fR for any \f(CW\*(C`x belongs to G\*(C'\fR there exists a unique family
\&\f(CW\*(C`[e_1,...,e_g]\*(C'\fR such that (no exceptions):
.PP
\&\-\- for \f(CW\*(C`1 <= i <= g\*(C'\fR we have \f(CW\*(C`0 <= e_i < o_i\*(C'\fR
.PP
\&\-\- \f(CW\*(C`x = g_1^{e_1}g_2^{e_2}...g_n^{e_n}\*(C'\fR
.PP
If present \f(CW\*(C`den\*(C'\fR must be a suitable value for \fIgal\fR\f(CW\*(C`[5]\*(C'\fR.
.PP
The library syntax is \fBgaloisinit\fR\f(CW\*(C`(\*(C'\fR\fIgal\fR\f(CW\*(C`,\*(C'\fR\fIden\fR\f(CW\*(C`)\*(C'\fR.
