that this is \s-1NOT\s0 the same as as \f(CW\*(C`idealpow(\*(C'\fR\fInf\fR\f(CW\*(C`,x,k)\*(C'\fR followed by
reduction, since the reduction is performed throughout the powering process.
.PP
The library syntax corresponding to \fIflag\fR\f(CW\*(C` = 0\*(C'\fR is
\&\fBidealpow\fR\f(CW\*(C`(\*(C'\fR\fInf\fR\f(CW\*(C`,x,k)\*(C'\fR. If \f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR is a \f(CW\*(C`long\*(C'\fR, you can use
\&\fBidealpows\fR\f(CW\*(C`(\*(C'\fR\fInf\fR\f(CW\*(C`,x,k)\*(C'\fR. Corresponding to \fIflag\fR\f(CW\*(C` = 1\*(C'\fR is
\&\fBidealpowred\fR\f(CW\*(C`(\*(C'\fR\fInf\fR\f(CW\*(C`,vp,k,\*(C'\fR\fIprec\fR\f(CW\*(C`)\*(C'\fR, where \fIprec\fR is a
