The library syntax is \fBidealval\fR\f(CW\*(C`(\*(C'\fR\fInf\fR\f(CW\*(C`,x,\*(C'\fR\fIvp\fR\f(CW\*(C`)\*(C'\fR, and the result is a \f(CW\*(C`long\*(C'\fR
integer.
.IX Xref "idealval"
.ie n .SS "ideleprincipal""(""\fInf\fP"",x)"""
.el .SS "ideleprincipal\f(CW(\fP\fInf\fP\f(CW,x)\fP"
.IX Xref "ideleprincipal"
.IX Subsection "ideleprincipal(nf,x)"
creates the principal idele
generated by the algebraic number \f(CW\*(C`x\*(C'\fR (which must be of type integer,
rational or polmod) in the number field \fInf\fR. The result is a
