.ie n .SS "rnfisnorm""(""\fIbnf\fP"",""\fIext\fP"",""\fIel\fP"",{""\fIflag\fP"" = 1})"""
.el .SS "rnfisnorm\f(CW(\fP\fIbnf\fP\f(CW,\fP\fIext\fP\f(CW,\fP\fIel\fP\f(CW,{\fP\fIflag\fP\f(CW = 1})\fP"
.IX Xref "rnfisnorm"
.IX Subsection "rnfisnorm(bnf,ext,el,{flag = 1})"
similar to
\&\f(CW\*(C`bnfisnorm\*(C'\fR but in the relative case. This tries to decide whether the
element \fIel\fR in \fIbnf\fR is the norm of some \f(CW\*(C`y\*(C'\fR in \fIext\fR.
\&\fIbnf\fR is as output by \f(CW\*(C`bnfinit\*(C'\fR.
.PP
\&\fIext\fR is a relative extension which has to be a row vector whose
components are:
.PP
\&\fIext\fR\f(CW\*(C`[1]\*(C'\fR: a relative equation of the number field \fIext\fR over
\&\fIbnf\fR. As usual, the priority of the variable of the polynomial
defining the ground field \fIbnf\fR (say \f(CW\*(C`y\*(C'\fR) must be lower than the
main variable of \fIext\fR\f(CW\*(C`[1]\*(C'\fR, say \f(CW\*(C`x\*(C'\fR.
.PP
\&\fIext\fR\f(CW\*(C`[2]\*(C'\fR: the generator \f(CW\*(C`y\*(C'\fR of the base field as a polynomial in \f(CW\*(C`x\*(C'\fR (as
given by \f(CW\*(C`rnfequation\*(C'\fR with \fIflag\fR\f(CW\*(C` = 1\*(C'\fR).
.PP
\&\fIext\fR\f(CW\*(C`[3]\*(C'\fR: is the \f(CW\*(C`bnfinit\*(C'\fR of the absolute extension \fIext\fR\f(CW\*(C`/\*(C'\fR\fBQ\fR.
.PP
This returns a vector \f(CW\*(C`[a,b]\*(C'\fR, where \fIel\fR\f(CW\*(C` = \*(C'\fR\fINorm\fR\f(CW\*(C`(a)*b\*(C'\fR. It looks for a
solution which is an \f(CW\*(C`S\*(C'\fR\-integer, with \f(CW\*(C`S\*(C'\fR a list of places (of \fIbnf\fR)
containing the ramified primes, the generators of the class group of
\&\fIext\fR, as well as those primes dividing \fIel\fR. If \fIext\fR\f(CW\*(C`/\*(C'\fR\fIbnf\fR
is known to be Galois, set \fIflag\fR\f(CW\*(C` = 0\*(C'\fR (here \fIel\fR is a norm iff \f(CW\*(C`b = 1\*(C'\fR).
If \fIflag\fR is non zero add to \f(CW\*(C`S\*(C'\fR all the places above the primes which: divide
\&\fIflag\fR if \fIflag\fR\f(CW\*(C` < 0\*(C'\fR, or are less than \fIflag\fR if \fIflag\fR\f(CW\*(C` > 0\*(C'\fR. The answer is guaranteed
(i.e.\ \fIel\fR is a norm iff \f(CW\*(C`b = 1\*(C'\fR) under \s-1GRH\s0, if \f(CW\*(C`S\*(C'\fR contains all
primes less than \f(CW12\fR \fIlog\fR \f(CW\*(C`^2|disc(\*(C'\fR\fIExt\fR\f(CW\*(C`)|\*(C'\fR, where
\&\fIExt\fR is the normal closure of \fIext\fR\f(CW\*(C` / \*(C'\fR\fIbnf\fR. Example:
.IX Xref "Galois GRH"
.PP
.Vb 5
\&  bnf = bnfinit(y^3 + y^2 \- 2*y \- 1);
\&  p = x^2 + Mod(y^2 + 2*y + 1, bnf.pol);
\&  rnf = rnfequation(bnf,p,1);
\&  ext = [p, rnf[2], bnfinit(rnf[1])];
\&  rnfisnorm(bnf,ext,17, 1)
.Ve
.PP
checks whether \f(CW17\fR is a norm in the Galois extension \fBQ\fR\f(CW\*(C`(\*(C'\fR\fIbeta\fR\f(CW\*(C`) /
\&\*(C'\fR\fBQ\fR\f(CW\*(C`(\*(C'\fR\fIalpha\fR\f(CW\*(C`)\*(C'\fR, where \fIalpha\fR\f(CW\*(C`^3 + \*(C'\fR\fIalpha\fR\f(CW\*(C`^2 \- 2\*(C'\fR\fIalpha\fR\f(CW\*(C` \- 1 = 0\*(C'\fR and \fIbeta\fR\f(CW\*(C`^2 +
\&\*(C'\fR\fIalpha\fR\f(CW\*(C`^2 + 2*\*(C'\fR\fIalpha\fR\f(CW\*(C` + 1 = 0\*(C'\fR (it is).
.PP
The library syntax is \fBrnfisnorm\fR\f(CW\*(C`(\*(C'\fR\fIbnf\fR\f(CW\*(C`,ext,x,\*(C'\fR\fIflag\fR\f(CW\*(C`,\*(C'\fR\fIprec\fR\f(CW\*(C`)\*(C'\fR.
.IX Xref "rnfisnorm"
